    <div id="thermal_desalination" class="product-solutions-image" style="background-image: url('<%= image_url('products/thermal-desalination.jpg')%>');">
      <h2 class="image-text">Thermal Desalination</h2>
    </div>
    <p>Innovations in the water industry play a crucial role in maintaining the supply of clean water. An example of this is Thermal Desalination: turning saltwater into water suitable for everyday human consumption. Modern desalination facilities employ the process of distillation through Multi-Stage Flash Distillation (MSF) and Multi-Effect Distillation (MED). Nowadays, desalinated seawater is one of the major alternatives to fresh water, helping address water scarcity in arid and dry regions such as the Middle East, North Africa and southern Europe.</p>
    <p><strong>JAS Global Industries’</strong> advanced thermal desalination solutions effectively manage and solve problems commonly associated with water desalination by MSF and MED processes. Being the only manufacturer of regionally approved Thermal Desalination chemical formulations – we take pride in being an essential partner to the Thermal Desalination industry in the MENA region by providing the most advanced and sustainable chemical solutions and services.</p>
    <p>Our UltraCareⓇ range of Antiscalants & Antifoulants, F-strikeⓇ Anti-foams, and OxyhuntⓇ Oxygen Scavengers have proven outstanding results in desalination plants throughout the MENA region.</p>
    <p>The product portfolio for Thermal Desalination includes:</p>
    <ul class="product-solutions-ul-first">
      <li>Antiscalants & Antifoulants</li>
      <li>Antifoams</li>
      <li>Oxygen Scavangers</li>
      <li>Acid Inhibitors</li>
      <li>Ion Exchange Resins – Anionic & Cationic</li>
    </ul>
    <p>JAS Global Industries also provides specialized technical service and support with both on-site dosage optimization and online monitoring technology applied to enhance monitoring of key operational performance parameters and live feedback.</p>
    <div id="reverse_osmosis" class="product-solutions-image" style="background-image: url('<%= image_url('products/reverse-osmosis.jpg')%>');">
      <h2 class="image-text">Reverse Osmosis</h2>
    </div>
    <p>Due to the high consumption of energy when heating the water in MSF and MED desalination systems, Membrane Desalination (Reverse Osmosis) processes utilizing specific membranes were developed and are implemented world-wide. Membrane Desalination systems are the most sustainable and cost-efficient way to meet this demand due to the recent improvements in desalination technology allowing the utilization of water from saline sources – typically brackish and seawater. Reverse Osmosis (RO) plants can successfully remove salt, bacteria, and other deposits from seawater and chemically treat the water to provide usable freshwater to meet the growing demand.</p>
    <p><strong>JAS Global Industries’</strong> advanced chemical additives are designed and formulated to enhance your membrane process to give you optimal results and protection even under challenging conditions.</p>
    <p>Our UltraCare® range, composed of a new generation of RO scale inhibitors, will enhance the efficiency of your membrane process. These Antiscalants and Antifoulants are specifically designed to remove all deposits and bacterial activity, as well as protect your operation against carbonate, sulphate, phosphate, and silica scaling. This will control bacterial activity at any pH, keeping your membrane surfaces efficiently clean from scale, even under the most challenging conditions.</p>
    <p>Our UltraFloc® range of polyamine, polydadmac, and polyacrylamide coagulants and flocculants will optimize your RO pre-treatment processes, including filtration, floatation, and settling processes. These enhanced processes effectively remove suspended sediment and improve your Silt Density Index (SDI) reduction.</p>
    <p>Our UltraClean® range is designed to keep your membrane clean throughout regular cleaning routines.</p>
    <p>The product portfolio for Reverse Osmosis includes:</p>
    <ul class="product-solutions-ul-first">
      <li>Antiscalants & Antifoulants</li>
